	<h1><strong>ABOUT</strong></h1>
	<div class="textContent">
		<div>
			<p>The New Museum’s Digital Archive is a groundbreaking project to document the activities and programmatic history of an institution. The digital material includes exhibition images, audio and video recordings of public programs, selected publications, curatorial checklists, brochures, press releases, and more. The Digital Archive continues to grow as a result of ongoing research and programming.</p>
		</div>
		<div>
			<p>Most materials are fully accessible to the public on the Internet, however some are available only at the New Museum's Resource Center due to copyright restriction or bandwidth requirements. Researchers are invited to visit our Resource Center on the 5th floor to access this material on site.</p>
		</div>
	<p><h2><strong>CONTACT</p></strong></h2>
