			<h2><strong>PLATFORM</strong></h2>
The New Museum Digital Archive was built using <a href="http://www.collectiveaccess.org" target="_ext">CollectiveAccess</a>, an open source, web-based software application to catalog, manage, and publish museum and archival collections. CollectiveAccess is developed by Whirl-i-Gig.  The Digital Archive is compliant with international standards, using qualified Dublin Core, and adhering to structured terminology outlined by Getty Vocabularies. CollectiveAccess is free software released under the GNU Public License, version 2. CollectiveAccess and changes in code from the New Museum Digital Archive project are free and available to the public or other institutions.</p>

